West Ham striker Diafra Sakho tore a thigh muscle against Stoke City on Saturday . 
  The 25-year-old has scored 12 goals this season but is out for the rest of the campaign . 
  Sakho was forced off after 59 minutes of the 1-1 draw at Upton Park . 
  The striker is West Ham's top scorer this season with 12 goals . 
  Sam Allardyce said he could return 'before the end of the season'